>[Question]
>i have read in a book if two lines meet at a point it is called 
>point of intersection and if more than two lines meet it is called 
>point of concurrancy.
>
>[Difficulty]
>now my problem is that can we call point of intersection point of 
>concurrancy
>
>[Thoughts]
>i read books and searched the web

Hi Farheen,

If any number of lines pass through a single point, the lines
intersect at that point, so it's correct to call it a point of
intersection.  

For most purposes, you can probably use 'intersection' and
'concurrency' as synonyms. 

